#87

Bulat Nasidze

*writes in Russian*

If Russians claim that their identity is supposedly based on godcentricity of centuries old and heavily influenced by Soviet times Era, then how the hell east Slavonic (Ukrainians and Belarussians) can claim to have anything in common with east Slavonic (Russians)?

By the same logic east Slavonics whom originally inhabited Ukraine and Belorousia for at least 1000 years had to share much of the same culture, language, feelings and so forth with the Russia regardless of the fact Russia hadn’t arrived into place till some steps later.

In other words, being closely related to Russians is NOT an obligatory condition to be an American national while citizens of Russia, Ukraine and Belorussia are bound to be Russians, Ukrainians or Belorussians for decades and even centuries to come.

In continuation:

The 2 primary tie factors of these lands were and are still the differing languages.

The rights we are discussing have nothing to do with language or nation. Money or any other country specific matter apparently.

Interesting what constitutes your “imperial”? Is owning the creation of money? Owning the seats of judges? Owning the jails? Owning the organs? This pic just stinks of the absolute worst feelings in the heart of a monster
